---
// ABOUTME: /about/ — first-person prose. Spine ported forward from the Hugo-era about page and updated to current role.
// ABOUTME: Voice is Esteban's. Tweak the prose directly in this file; structure + styling stay.

import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import mePhoto from '../assets/me.png';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Head of Platform Engineering at Zenjob. Costa Rican transplanted to Berlin."
  current="about"
>
  <article class="about-page">
    <header class="about-page__header reveal">
      <h1 class="about-page__title">About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="about-page__body">
      <figure class="about-page__photo reveal" aria-hidden="false">
        <Image
          src={mePhoto}
          alt="Esteban Torres — selfie styled as a Spotify 'This Is' playlist cover."
          widths={[280, 420, 560, 840]}
          sizes="(max-width: 720px) min(320px, 100vw), 280px"
          loading="eager"
          fetchpriority="high"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>

      <div class="prose about-page__prose reveal">
        <p>
          Hi; my name is <strong>Esteban Torres</strong> and I'm currently
          <code>Head of Platform Engineering</code> at
          <a href="https://zenjob.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Zenjob</a>, in Berlin.
        </p>

        <p>
          I'm originally from 🇨🇷 Costa Rica, where I started as an
          <code>Engineer</code> and quickly jumped on the <code>iOS</code> bandwagon. That led me to a
          job as an <code>iOS</code> engineer at
          <a href="https://soundcloud.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">SoundCloud</a>, which led to me
          and my family moving to 🇩🇪.
        </p>

        <p>
          During my time at SoundCloud I wore many hats: <code>iOS</code> engineer (<code
            >Listening Cluster</code
          >, then <code>Core Clients</code>), <code>Cross Platform</code> engineer (<code
            >Core Clients</code
          >, where I got to do <code>Scala</code>, <code>Go</code>, some
          <code>Production Engineering</code>, <code>iOS</code> and <code>Android</code> development),
          and eventually <code>Engineering Manager</code> for
          <code>Back-End Engineering Productivity</code> alongside Core Clients. The team looked after
          <code>JVMKit</code>, the shared platform behind 200+ microservices.
        </p>

        <p>
          From SoundCloud I jumped to
          <a href="https://spotify.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Spotify</a>, leading a very
          distributed team across Sweden, the UK, Germany, Colorado, and New York working on
          <a href="https://backstage.spotify.com" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            ><code>Backstage</code></a
          >. We shipped the first three monetised plugins and laid the foundations for the plugin
          marketplace, which became a new revenue stream for Spotify.
        </p>

        <p>
          After Spotify I joined <a href="https://zenjob.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Zenjob</a>
          as <code>Engineering Manager</code> for the Platform &amp; DevOps team, was promoted to
          <code>Head of Engineering</code> for the Supply vertical (3 EMs, 30+ engineers) bridging a company-wide
          <code>React Native</code> migration, and now I'm
          <code>Head of Platform Engineering</code>, supporting 60+ product engineers across the
          company on infrastructure, observability, developer tooling, and an org-wide rollout of
          AI-assisted development (<code>Copilot</code>, <code>Cursor</code>, <code
            >Claude Code</code
          >).
        </p>

        <p>
          I used to be moderately active in the <code>iOS</code> community and tried to attend different
          conferences (as an attendee as well as a speaker) but since I switched careers I've slowed down
          a lot on that front.
        </p>

        <p>
          It's been a few years since I started working as an <code>Engineering Manager</code> and lots
          of things have happened along the way. The day-to-day has shifted from "I have no idea what
          I am doing" to "I have no idea what I am doing, but I've seen this before". I haven't stopped
          coding either; these days mostly <code>Go</code>, <code>Node.js</code>, and <code
            >TypeScript</code
          >, with a fair amount of <code>gRPC</code> and
          <code>NATS</code> on side projects like
          <a href="https://quik.so" rel="noopener noreferrer">Quik</a> (a production AI agent platform)
          and <a href="https://bluetip.ai" rel="noopener noreferrer">BlueTip</a>
          (multi-provider LLM writing tool).
        </p>

        <p>
          I've been jotting down what I learn in a good old paper notebook which I'll try to migrate
          to a more modern place on this website.
        </p>

        <p class="about-page__contact">
          <strong>Best way to reach me</strong>: email at
          <a href="mailto:me@estebantorr.es">me@estebantorr.es</a>. Elsewhere lives in the footer:
          GitHub, Mastodon, LinkedIn, Bluesky, RSS.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <nav class="about-page__elsewhere" aria-label="More on this site">
      <p class="about-page__elsewhere-label">More on this site</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/blog/">Writing</a></li>
        <li><a href="/cv/">CV</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: var(--max-content);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
  }

  .about-page__header {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .about-page__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: var(--text-h1);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }

  /* Two-column body on desktop (prose left, photo right). Stacks on mobile
     with the photo on top (source order: photo first, prose second, so the
     stack lands photo → prose naturally). */
  .about-page__body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    align-items: start;
  }

  @media (min-width: 720px) {
    .about-page__body {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 280px;
      column-gap: var(--space-xl);
    }
    .about-page__prose {
      grid-column: 1;
      grid-row: 1;
    }
    .about-page__photo {
      grid-column: 2;
      grid-row: 1;
    }
  }

  .about-page__photo {
    margin: 0;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 320px;
    aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .about-page__photo :global(img) {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  /* Reuse .prose typography (Vollkorn body + Bricolage headings) — same module the
     article body uses. The only tweak: a slightly tighter top margin on the first
     paragraph so the h1 sits closer to the lede. */
  .about-page__prose :global(p:first-child) {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .about-page__contact {
    margin-top: var(--space-md);
    padding-top: var(--space-md);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }

  .about-page__contact :global(strong) {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .about-page__elsewhere {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    max-width: var(--measure);
  }

  .about-page__elsewhere-label {
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-sm);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-meta);
    color: var(--ink-muted);
    letter-spacing: 0.005em;
  }

  .about-page__elsewhere ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-small);
  }

  .about-page__elsewhere a {
    color: var(--ink);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: color-mix(in oklab, var(--accent) 50%, transparent);
    text-underline-offset: 0.2em;
    transition:
      color var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out-quart),
      text-decoration-color var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out-quart);
  }

  .about-page__elsewhere a:hover,
  .about-page__elsewhere a:focus-visible {
    color: var(--accent-ink);
    text-decoration-color: currentColor;
  }
</style>
